MATCH_TOOL: Edit|Write
MATCH_PATTERN: apps/client/src/cartridges/.+Renderer\.tsx$
MATCH_CONTENT: (requestAnimationFrame|performance\.now\(\)|lastTime(Ref)?\.current)
ADVISORY: |
  When computing dt from `requestAnimationFrame`'s `now` minus a prior
  timestamp, clamp dt ≥ 0. Chrome can pass a `now` value earlier than
  `performance.now()` captured during the effect setup — producing a
  small negative dt on the first frame.

  Common symptom: game state drifts slightly negative (distance,
  elapsed, score), and any `Math.floor(negative)` used as an array
  index returns -1 → `ARRAY[-1] = undefined` → downstream crash.

  Safe pattern:
    const rawDtMs = Math.max(0, Math.min(50, now - lastTimeRef.current));
    lastTimeRef.current = now;

  Or: initialize `lastTimeRef.current = now` on the first frame instead
  of in the effect body.

  This bit Gap Run on 2026-04-12 — the crash surfaced as
  "Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'startsWith')" from
  withAlpha(zoneColor, ...) because `ZONES[-1]` was undefined.

  Kill condition: delete once all arcade renderers have been audited
  and the `Math.max(0, ...)` clamp is either present at every `dt =
  now - lastTime` site or replaced with a shared RAF-dt helper.
